(6, 1, 'php-print', 'PHP Print', '		  		  <h1>Learn PHP Print</h1><p><span style=\" \">Print&nbsp; is&nbsp; output key. It sends no matter what is in the quotations (or parentheses) that adhere to it to the result device (browser window). A new similar function is indicate, but print allows the particular user to check whether or not the print succeeded.</span></p><p>PHP print statement works extremely well to be able to print single line string, multi line strings, escaping characters, array etc.</p><div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>Syntax of PHP print:</b>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --></p><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><table><tbody><tr><td><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\">1\n2\n3</pre></td><td><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"><!--?php</span--> &lt;?php\nint <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">print</span>(string <span style=\"color: #003333\">$arg</span>)    \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</span></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n\n\n<p></p></div><p>Typically the quoted text is handled as if it were a string, and so works extremely well in conjunction with the concatenation (joining 2 strings together) operator since well as any perform that returns a thread value.</p><div><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-weight: bolder; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 13.3333px;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" rgb(255,=\"\" 255,=\"\" 255);\"=\"\">Example Printing Single string:</span></div><div><font color=\"#212529\"><b><br></b></font>\n