(7, 1, 'php-use-of-variable', 'PHP learn - Variables', '		  <h1>Learn PHP Variable</h1><p>A variable is a memory location that hold data.Variable used to store data inside temporary .In PHP ,we declare variable using (<b>$).</b><b><br></b>Syntax of desclaring a variable:</p>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"><!--?php</span-->&lt;?php    \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$variable</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"Any Value\"</span>;   \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</span></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></div><br><h1>PHP Variable to store string, integer and float</h1><div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">See the diffrent examples of variable decration:</p>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"><!--?php</span-->&lt;?php  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$str</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"I am Akshay\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">220</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$b</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">41.6</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"string is: </span><span style=\"color: #AA0000\">$str</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\"> <br>\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"integer value is: </span><span style=\"color: #AA0000\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\"> <br>\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"float value is : </span><span style=\"color: #AA0000\">$b</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\"> <br>\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #555555\">?</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">&gt;</span>  \n</span></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>Output:</b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);margin: 8px 0px 0px;background: rgb(249, 251, 249);padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px;font-family: verdana;font-size: 13px;text-align: justify;\"><pre>string is: I am Akshay\ninteger value is: 220&nbsp;\nfloat value is: 41.6&nbsp;</pre></div><br><h1>PHP add the values inside variables</h1>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"><!--?php</span-->&lt;?php  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">10</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$b</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">20</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$c</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">+</span><span style=\"color: #003333\">$b</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$c</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</span></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p style=\"text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\">Output:</span></b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);margin: 8px 0px 0px;background: rgb(249, 251, 249);padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px;font-family: verdana;font-size: 13px;text-align: justify;\"><pre>30</pre></div><br><h1>PHP case senstive Variables</h1><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Inside PHP variables are case sensitive that mean&nbsp; <b>$Name</b>&nbsp; and <b>$<span style=\"font-family: verdana;\">NAME</span></b><span style=\"font-family: verdana;\">&nbsp;are two diffrent variables . I you use diffrent name or not the same variable name ,it will show you error . Shown below:</span>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --></p><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"><!--?php</span-->&lt;?php  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$name</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"akshay\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"My name is \"</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$color</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"<br>\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"My name is \"</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$NAME</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"<br>\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"My name is \"</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$naME</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"<br>\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</span></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n\n\n<p></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>Output:</b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);margin: 8px 0px 0px;background: rgb(249, 251, 249);padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px;font-family: verdana;font-size: 13px;text-align: justify;\"><pre style=\"\n\">My car is akshay\nNotice: Undefined variable: NAME in C:\\wamp\\www\\variable.php on line 4\nMy name is \nNotice: Undefined variable: naME in C:\\wamp\\www\\variable.php on line 5\nMy name is </pre></div><br><h1>PHP invalid Variables</h1><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Some variables are invalid inside PHP .That means PHP dont accept them and show error.</p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Shown Below:</p>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php \n<span style=\"color: #AA0000; background-color: #FFAAAA\">$</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">12</span>c<span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"hi there\"</span>;<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">//number in begining (invalid)  </span>\n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$c12</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"hi there again \"</span>;<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">//number after text (valid)  </span>\n<span style=\"color: #AA0000; background-color: #FFAAAA\">$</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">*</span>data<span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"hi there\"</span>;<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">//special symbol (invalid)  </span>\n  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"$12c <br> $*data <br>\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$c12</span>;\n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</span></pre></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>Output:</b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);margin: 8px 0px 0px;background: rgb(249, 251, 249);padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px;font-family: verdana;font-size: 13px;text-align: justify;\"><pre>Parse error: syntax error, unexpected \'4\' (T_LNUMBER), expecting variable (T_VARIABLE)\n or \'$\' in C:\\wamp\\www\\variableinvalid.php on line 2\n</pre><pre>hi there</pre><div><br></div></div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">&nbsp;I Hope you understand the concept behind Variables . If yes continue to next lesson :)</p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></p></div> \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'php variable,php session variables,php variables,	php static variable,	php declare variable,php global variables,php echo variable,php variable scope', 'Learn use PHP Variable inside PHP', 'A variable is a memory location that hold data.Variable used to store data inside temporary .In PHP ,we declare variable using ($).', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(8, 1, 'php-use-dollar-doubledollar', 'PHP learn - $ & $$', '		  		  <h1>Learn $ (Single Dollar ) and $$ (Double Dollar)</h1><p></p><p><b>$variable (Single Dollar):</b> This is a normal variable to store the values like string,float,integer etc.<br></p><p><b>$$variable (Double Dollar) :</b> This reference variable keep the value of $variable&nbsp; as a variable name .</p><p>To know more See this Example:\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --></p><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><table><tbody><tr><td></td><td><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span>  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"vardata\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span> <span style=\"color: #FF6600\">10</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"&lt;/br&gt;\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"&lt;/br&gt;\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$vardata</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</pre></td></tr></tbody></table></div><div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \" segoe=\"\" ui\",=\"\" roboto,=\"\" \"helvetica=\"\" neue\",=\"\" arial,=\"\" sans-serif,=\"\" \"apple=\"\" color=\"\" emoji\",=\"\" \"segoe=\"\" ui=\"\" symbol\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 13.3333px;=\"\" background-color:=\"\" rgb(255,=\"\" 255,=\"\" 255);\"=\"\"><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><font color=\"#212529\" face=\"verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\">&nbsp;</span></font><br><span style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bolder;\">Output:</span><b style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\"><br></b>vardata<br>10<br>10</p><p style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 2; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\"><b style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" font-size:=\"\" medium;=\"\" text-align:=\"\" start;\"=\"\">Next Example:</b>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --></p><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span>  \n <span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"Akshay\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"Dhiman\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"&lt;/br&gt;\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"&lt;/br&gt;\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"Last name of </span><span style=\"color: #AA0000\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\"> is \"</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$$a</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</pre></div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify;\"><b style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;</b></p><p><b style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Output:</b><b style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;\"><br></b>Akshay<br>Dhiman<br>Last Name of Akshay is Dhiman</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; line-height: 2;\">In above example we again did the same , we assign the value Akshay in variable $a and reference variable $$a assigned as Dhiman.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; line-height: 2;\"><br></p><p style=\"color: rgb(33, 37, 41); box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 2; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\"><br></p></div> \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'php single and double dollor,php $ ,php $$,php to dollar,dollar to php,dollar to php peso,what is php,php,dollar', 'Learn use of  PHP $ (Single Dollar ) and $$ (Double Dollar)', '  $variable (Single Dollar): This is a normal variable to store the values like string,float,integer etc.  $$variable (Double Dollar) : This reference variabl  ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(9, 1, 'php-Constants', 'PHP learn - Constants', '		  <h1>Learn PHP Constants&nbsp;</h1><p>PHP constants can be name, variable or identifier that can not be change on execution time . This can be define in two ways :</p><div><ul><li>Using : define() Function</li><li>Using : Const</li></ul><p>PHP constants can be useful while database connection , where you can define the values once that later can not be changed during execution. PHP constant follow the same PHP rules,variables can only start with&nbsp; letters or underscores.</p><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;text-align: justify;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>See This Example</b>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --></p><div style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow: auto; width: auto; border-style: solid; border-color: gray; border-image: initial; border-width: 0.1em 0.1em 0.1em 0.8em; padding: 0.2em 0.6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 125%;\"><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243); color: rgb(0, 153, 153);\">&lt;?php</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243);\">  \n</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243); color: rgb(51, 102, 102);\">define</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243);\">(names, </span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243); color: rgb(0, 102, 153); font-weight: bold;\">case</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243); color: rgb(85, 85, 85);\">-</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243);\">insensitive, values)  \n</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243); color: rgb(0, 153, 153);\">?&gt;</span><span style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 243, 243);\">  </span>\n</pre></div></div><p><span style=\" \">Name: It define the name of constant&nbsp;<br></span><span style=\"\">Case-Insensitive :&nbsp;</span>It define the&nbsp; constant value<br><span style=\"\">Value: It give option to change case sensitive&nbsp;, By default FASLE ( It means case sensitive)</span></p><div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;text-align: justify;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>See this example To know Better</b>\n\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --></p><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span>  \n<span style=\"color: #336666\">define</span>(<span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"NAME\"</span>,<span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"Akshay\"</span>);  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> NAME;  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</pre></div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;text-align: justify;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>Output:</b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);width: 657.6px;margin: 8px 0px 0px;background: rgb(249, 251, 249);padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px;font-family: verdana;text-align: justify;\"><pre>Akshay</pre></div><span class=\"filename\" style=\"font-style: italic;font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;text-align: justify;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></span></div><div><font face=\"verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 13px;\"><br></span></font></div><div><font face=\"verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"\"><b>See Another Example&nbsp;&nbsp;</b>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span>  \n<span style=\"color: #336666\">define</span>(<span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"NAME\"</span>,<span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"Hello I am akshay\"</span>,<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">true</span>);<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">//not case sensitive  </span>\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> NAME<span style=\"color: #555555\">.</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\'&lt;.br&gt;\'</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> name;  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</pre></div></span></font></div><div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>&nbsp;Output:</b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198); width: 657.6px; margin: 8px 0px 0px; background: rgb(249, 251, 249); padding: 0px 0px 0px 5px; font-family: verdana; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify;\"><pre><span style=\"font-family: verdana; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Hello&nbsp;I am akshay</span></pre><pre><span style=\"font-family: verdana; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Hello&nbsp;I am akshay</span></pre></div><h2 style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></h2><h2 style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;text-align: justify;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">WOW you are learning fast . May be you are genius :)</h2><span class=\"filename\" style=\"font-style: italic; font-size: 14px; font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"></span></div> \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'php const,php constant variable,php redefine constant,php constant function,php,constant,what is php,learn php', 'Learn use of PHP Constants inside PHP', ' PHP constants can be name, variable or identifier that can not be change on execution time . This can be define in two ways  ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay');
