(13, 1, 'php-comments', 'PHP learn - Comments', '		  <h1>PHP learn - Comments \n		   \n		   \n		  </h1><div>In easy words , PHP comments are used to describe about the code so that another developer can understand the code easily .Also you can hide the unwanted code using comment .<br><br>If you comment the code then it will be non excitable .</div><div><br></div><div><b>See this Example :</b></div><div>&nbsp;</div>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"><!--?php</span-->&lt;?php \n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">//this is my name </span>\n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$name</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span>  <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"Akshay Dhiman\"</span>;\n\n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">// This code is not executable</span>\n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">// $commented_name =  \"Akshay Dhiman\";</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #003333\">$name</span> ; \n\n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>\n</span></pre></div>&nbsp;<div><p><b>Output:</b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);  \">Akshay Dhiman</div></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Inside PHP you can comment in two ways :&nbsp;<br><br><ul><li><b>Single Line Comment&nbsp;</b></li><li><b>Multi-line&nbsp;Comment&nbsp;</b></li></ul></div><h2><b><br></b>Single line Comment&nbsp;</h2><div>Now there is two ways to comment :</div><div><ol><li><b>( // )&nbsp;</b>- This is one way to comment single line&nbsp;<b>(c++ style)</b></li><li><b>( # )</b> - This another way to comment <b>(Unix shell style)</b></li></ol></div><div><b>See this Example:</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"><!--?php</span-->  \n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">// This is one way to comment single line (c++ style)  </span>\n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\"># This another way to comment (Unix shell style)  </span>\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\" Single line comment\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</span></pre></div>&nbsp;<div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>Output:</b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);  \">Single Line Comment</div></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><h2>Multi line Comment&nbsp;</h2></div><div>Inside PHP we can also comment multi lines . We can use (&nbsp;<b>/* i am comment text */ )</b> star and slash&nbsp; like this . Let us how you one example .</div><div><br></div><div><b>Example :</b></div><div><br></div><div></div><!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php <!--?php</span-->  \n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">/* </span>\n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">Everything inside is comment . Multi-lines supported that drop to next lines.</span>\n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">*/</span>  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"Multi line comment\"</span>;  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  &nbsp;</span></pre></div><div><p style=\"font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; text-align: justify; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><b>Output:</b></p><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);\">Multi line comment</div></div>&nbsp;&nbsp; \n		  ', 'php, tutorial, php comments, php comment, session, date, array, functions, time, xml, ajax, mysql, mysql, regex, string, oop', 'PHP comments - jQuerylearn', 'PHP Comments examples  with some practical experiments . php file, php session, php date, php array, php form, functions, time, xml, ajax, php mysql, regex, string, oop', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(15, 2, 'php-If-Else', 'PHP learn - If Else', '<h1>Learn PHP IF Else</h1><div><br></div><div>PHP If else is very interesting topic when you start programming . If Else is&nbsp; used to test and create a logic of your website .</div><div><br></div><div>If Else is statement and there is various ways to use it :</div><div><br></div><div><ul><li>If&nbsp;</li><li>If-else</li><li>elseif</li><li>nested If&nbsp;</li></ul><h2>If statement&nbsp;</h2></div><div>This statement is executable when the condition you applied is true .</div><div><br></div><div><b>For example</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div></div><!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"> &lt;?php</span>  \n\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">if</span> (<span style=\"color: #FF6600\">10</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">==</span> <span style=\"color: #FF6600\">10</span>)\n{\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\'true\'</span>;\n}\n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</pre></div>&nbsp;&nbsp;<div><br></div><div><b>Output:&nbsp;</b><b>true&nbsp;</b></div><div><br></div><div><h2>If&nbsp; Else statement&nbsp;&nbsp;</h2></div><div></div>\n\n\nIn this statement we check<b> if $a is 10</b> then <b>write true</b> else <b>write&nbsp;false</b><div><br><!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span>\n<span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">10</span>;\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">if</span>(<span style=\"color: #003333\">$a</span> <span style=\"color: #555555\">==</span> <span style=\"color: #FF6600\">10</span>)\n{  \n   <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"true\"</span>;\n}\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">else</span>\n{  \n   <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">else</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"False\"</span>  ;\n}  \n</pre></div>&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><div><b>Output:&nbsp;</b><b>true&nbsp;</b></div></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>If you want to know more in detail then see this video&nbsp;</b></div><div><b><br></b></div>&nbsp;<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/YuQZDiawu3A\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>&nbsp;', 'php, tutorial, example, file, session, date, array, functions, time, xml, ajax, mysql, mysql, regex, string, oop', 'PHP If Else - jQueryLearn', 'PHP if else  with examples and practical experiments , php file, php session, php date, php array, php form, functions, time, xml, ajax, php mysql, regex, string, oop', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(16, 2, 'php-switch', 'PHP learn - Switch', '<h1>Learn PHP Switch&nbsp;</h1><div>It is same like If else statement . In <b>PHP switch</b> statement , it execute <b>single statement</b> from <b>multiple conditions</b> .</div><div><br></div><div><b>For example&nbsp;</b></div><div><br></div>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span> \n\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">switch</span>(expression)\n{      \n   <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">case</span> value1<span style=\"color: #555555\">:</span>    \n   <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">break</span>;  \n\n   <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">case</span> value2<span style=\"color: #555555\">:</span>    \n   <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">break</span>;  \n \n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">// It execute the matching result   </span>\n}  \n\n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Now let me give you one <b>example&nbsp; </b>of <b>switch statement </b>with<b> output :</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Suppose $i = cake :</b></div><div><br></div><div>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span>\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">switch</span> (<span style=\"color: #003333\">$i</span>) {\n    <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">case</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"apple\"</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">:</span>\n        <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"i is apple\"</span>;\n        <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">break</span>;\n    <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">case</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"bar\"</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">:</span>\n        <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"i is bar\"</span>;\n        <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">break</span>;\n    <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">case</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"cake\"</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">:</span>\n        <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"i is cake\"</span>;\n        <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">break</span>;\n}\n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n</div><div><b><br></b></div><h2><b><br></b><b>Guess what will be output ?</b></h2><div><b>You are right : cake&nbsp;</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>so easy right ? :)</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>TO know more see this video :</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b><br></b></div>\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NP6tBCZfXls\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe>', 'php, tutorial, example, file, session, date, array, functions, time, xml, ajax, mysql, mysql, regex, string, oop', 'PHP Switch - jQuerylearn', 'PHP switch  with examples and practical experiments , php file, php session, php date, php array, php form, functions, time, xml, ajax, php mysql, regex, string, oop', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(17, 2, 'php-for-loop', 'PHP learn - For Loop', '<h1>Learn PHP&nbsp; For Loop&nbsp;</h1><div>PHP For Loop&nbsp; is used to execute the code up to specific number.</div><div><br></div><div>If you already know the last value then use it otherwise use while Loop.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span>\n\n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">for</span>(initialization; condition; increment<span style=\"color: #555555\">/</span>decrement){  \n<span style=\"color: #0099FF; font-style: italic\">//code execute here </span>\n}  \n\n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>&nbsp;<div><br></div><div><b>Lets do practice with an example&nbsp;</b></div><div><b><br></b></div>\n\n<!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\">&lt;?php</span>  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">for</span>(<span style=\"color: #003333\">$i</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">1</span>;<span style=\"color: #003333\">$i</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">&lt;=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">5</span>;<span style=\"color: #003333\">$i</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">++</span>){  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"</span><span style=\"color: #AA0000\">$i</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">&lt;br/&gt;\"</span>;  \n}  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</pre></div>&nbsp;<div>In above example the code will execute until the value is 5 (&nbsp;<b>$i = 5 ;)</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><div class=\"codeblock3\" style=\"border: 1px solid rgb(213, 221, 198);  \"><pre> 1\n 2\n 3\n 4\n 5<br></pre></div></div>&nbsp;<div>See this so easy right ?</div><div><br></div><div>Don\'t say no . hehe&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><b>Lets do another example&nbsp; with nested :</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div>In PHP , you can use for loop inside for loop . We call this <b>nested loop .&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></div><div><br></div><div></div><!-- HTML generated using hilite.me --><div style=\"background: #f0f3f3; overflow:auto;width:auto;border:solid gray;border-width:.1em .1em .1em .8em;padding:.2em .6em;\"><pre style=\"margin: 0; line-height: 125%\"><span style=\"color: #009999\"> &lt;?php</span>  \n<span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">for</span>(<span style=\"color: #003333\">$i</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">1</span>;<span style=\"color: #003333\">$i</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">&lt;=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">4</span>;<span style=\"color: #003333\">$i</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">++</span>) \n{  \n    <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">for</span>(<span style=\"color: #003333\">$b</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">1</span>;<span style=\"color: #003333\">$b</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">&lt;=</span><span style=\"color: #FF6600\">4</span>;<span style=\"color: #003333\">$b</span><span style=\"color: #555555\">++</span>)\n       {  \n        <span style=\"color: #006699; font-weight: bold\">echo</span> <span style=\"color: #CC3300\">\"</span><span style=\"color: #AA0000\">$i</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">   </span><span style=\"color: #AA0000\">$b</span><span style=\"color: #CC3300\">&lt;br/&gt;\"</span>;  \n       }  \n}  \n<span style=\"color: #009999\">?&gt;</span>  \n</pre></div>&nbsp;<div><div><b>Outer Loop Execute 4 Times .</b></div><div><b>Inside loop execute 4 times inside outer loop . Oute