(68, 7, 'html-element', 'HTML elements', '		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  <h1>HTML element</h1><div>HTML documents are defined by HTML elements.</div><h2>HTML element</h2><div>The HTML element refers to all the code from the start tag to the end tag.</div><div><br>To the following</div><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><tbody><tr><td><b>&nbsp;<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(20, 25, 30); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, 微软雅黑, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(237, 241, 242); line-height: 1.76em;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Start tag</font></font></span></b></td><td><b>&nbsp;<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(20, 25, 30); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, 微软雅黑, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(237, 241, 242); line-height: 1.76em;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Element content</font></font></span></b></td><td><b>End tag</b></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;p&gt;</td><td>This is a paragraph</td><td>&lt;/p&gt;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp; &lt;a href=\"\" &gt;</td><td>&lt;itd&gt;</td><td>&nbsp;&lt;/body&gt;</td></tr></tbody></table><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br><b>Note</b>: Start tags are often referred to as opening tags, and end tags are often referred to as closing tags.<br><br></div><h2 style=\"\">HTML element syntax</h2><ul><li style=\"text-align: left;\">HTML element starts with a start tag<br><br></li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">HTML element terminated with end tag<br><br></li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">The content of the element is the content between the start tag and the end tag<br><br></li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Some HTML elements have empty content<br><br></li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Empty elements are closed in the start tag (ends with the end of the start tag)<br><br></li><li style=\"text-align: left;\">Most HTML elements can have attributes</li></ul><div style=\"text-align: left;\">Tip: You\'ll learn more about properties in the next chapter of this tutorial.<br><br></div><h2 style=\"\">Nested HTML elements</h2><div style=\"text-align: left;\">Most HTML elements can be nested (can contain other HTML elements).</div><div style=\"text-align: left;\">HTML documents consist of nested HTML elements.</div>\n\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\"> \n	&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;  \n	&lt;html&gt;  \n	&lt;head&gt;  \n	&lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;  \n	&lt;title&gt;jquerylearn(jquerylearn.com)&lt;/title&gt;  \n	&lt;/head&gt;  \n	&lt;body&gt;  \n	 &lt;p&gt;There are three html elements&lt;/p&gt;&nbsp;  \n	&lt;/body&gt;  \n	&lt;/html&gt;  \n	 \n	 </textarea>\n </form>\n\n<br><div style=\"\">The above example contains three HTML elements. Are &lt;p&gt; elements, &lt;body&gt; elements, &lt;html&gt; elements</div><div style=\"\"><br><h2 style=\"\">HTML instance explanation</h2></div><pre><span style=\"line-height: 1.76em; vertical-align: inherit;\"><b>&lt;p&gt; Element:</b></span><strong><font><font><font color=\"#1f2426\" face=\"Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, PingFang SC, 微软雅黑, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; background-color: rgb(237, 241, 242); line-height: 1.76em; vertical-align: inherit;\"><br><br><br>\n</span></font></font></font></strong>&lt;p&gt;this is my first paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;<br>This &lt;p&gt; element defines a paragraph in the HTML document.<br>This element has a start tag &lt;p&gt; and an end tag&lt;/p&gt;.</pre><div style=\"text-align: left;\">The element content is: this is my first paragraph.</div><div><br></div><pre><b>&lt;body&gt; element:<font color=\"#000000\" face=\"Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">\n</span></font></b>&lt;body&gt;&nbsp;<br>&lt;p&gt;dis is my first paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;&nbsp;<br>&lt;/body&gt;<br>The &lt;body&gt; element defines the body of the HTML document.<br>This element has a start tag &lt;body&gt; and an end tag &lt;/body&gt;.</pre><div style=\"text-align: left;\">The element content is another HTML element (p element).</div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><pre style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>&lt;html&gt; element:</b><br>&lt;html&gt;&nbsp;<br>&lt;body&gt;&nbsp;<br>&lt;p&gt;This is my first paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;&nbsp;<br>&lt;/body&gt;&nbsp;<br>&lt;/html&gt;<br>The &lt;html&gt; element defines the entire HTML document.<br>This element has a start tag &lt;html&gt; and an end tag&lt;/html&gt;.</pre><div style=\"text-align: left;\">The element content is another HTML element (the body element).</div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Don\'t forget to end the label</h2><div style=\"text-align: left;\">Even if you forget to use the end tag, most browsers will display the HTML correctly:</div><div style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</div><pre style=\"text-align: left;\">&lt;p&gt;this&nbsp;is a paragraph</pre><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>Instance</b></div>\n\n\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;  \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;  \n&lt;head&gt;  \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;  \n    &lt;title&gt;php.cn&lt;/title&gt;  \n&lt;/head&gt;  \n&lt;body&gt;  \n&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph  \n&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph  \n&lt;/body&gt;  \n&lt;/html&gt; \n	 \n	 </textarea>\n </form>\n\n<br><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><b><br>Program running result:</b></div><p style=\"text-align: left;\">This is a paragraph<br>This is a paragraph &nbsp; &nbsp;</p><div style=\"text-align: left;\">The above example is fine in most browsers, but don\'t rely on it. Forgetting to use the end tag can produce unpredictable results or errors.</div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>Note </b>: Future HTML versions do not allow omitting the end tag.</div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">Empty HTML element</h2><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\">HTML elements without content are called empty elements. Empty elements are turned off in the start tag.</div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><pre style=\"text-align: left;\">&lt;br&gt; is an empty element that does not close the tag (&lt;br&gt; tag defines a line break).</pre><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><div style=\"text-align: left;\">In XHTML, XML, and future versions of HTML, all elements must be closed.</div><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><pre style=\"text-align: left;\">Adding slashes to the opening tag, such as &lt;br /&gt;, is the correct way to turn off empty elements. HTML, XHTML, and XML all accept this.</pre><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><pre style=\"text-align: left;\">Even though &lt;br&gt; is effective in all browsers, using &lt;br /&gt; is a longer-term guarantee.</pre><div style=\"text-align: left;\"><br></div><pre style=\"text-align: left;\"><b>Tip </b>: HTML tags are not case sensitive: &lt;P&gt; is equivalent to &lt;p&gt;, but lowercase is recommended</pre>		  		   <br>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML element | jquerylearn.com', '  HTML element starts with a start tag  HTML element terminated with end tag  The content of the element is the content between the start tag and the end tag  Some HTML elements have empty content  Empty elements are closed in the start tag (ends with the end of the start tag)  ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(69, 7, 'html-attributes', 'HTML attributes', '		  		  		  		  		  		  		  <h1>HTML attribute</h1>\n<div>HTML tags can have attributes. Attributes provide more information about HTML elements.</div><div><br></div><div>Attributes always appear as name/value pairs, such as: <b>name=\"value\".</b></div><div><br></div><div>Attributes are always specified in the start tag of the HTML element.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>HTML links are defined by the &lt;a&gt; tag. The address of the link is specified in the href attribute:</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;a href=\"http://www.jquerylearn.com\"&gt;This is a link&lt;/a&gt;</div><br>\n\n\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;www.jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body&gt; \n    &lt;a href=\"www.jquerylearn.com\"&gt;This is a link&lt;/a&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n\n	 </textarea>\n </form>\n\n\n<div>Examples explain: by clicking on the above \"This is a link\" will jump to &nbsp;http://www.w3school.com.cn &nbsp;this site<br><br></div><h2>Property example 1:</h2><div>&lt;h1&gt; Defines the beginning of the title.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;php.cn&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body&gt; \n&lt;h1 align=\"center\"&gt;Title&lt;/h1&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n	 </textarea>\n </form>\n\n<div><b>Explanation</b>: Center the &lt;h1&gt; heading title<br><br></div><h2>Property example 2:</h2><div>&lt;body&gt; Defines the body of the HTML document.</div><br>\n\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\"> \n \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;php.cn&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body bgcolor=\"yellow\"&gt;hiiiiiiiiii&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n \n	 </textarea>\n </form>\n\n<div><b>Explanation</b>: The above code means to set the background color of the webpage to yellow.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Hint </b>: Attributes and attribute values ​​are not case sensitive. The new version of (X)HTML requires a lowercase attribute.<br><br></div><h2>Always quote the attribute value</h2><div>Property values ​​should always be enclosed in quotes. Double quotes are the most commonly used, but there is no problem with single quotes.</div><div><br></div><div>In some individual cases, such as attribute values ​​themselves with double quotes, you must use single quotes, for example:</div><div><br></div><div><b>Name=\'Bill \"HelloWorld\" Gates\'<br><br></b></div><h2>HTML Property Reference Manual</h2><div>Our complete HTML reference manual provides a complete list of legal properties that can be used by each HTML element:</div><div><br></div><div>Complete HTML reference manual</div><div><br></div><div>The properties that apply to most HTML elements are listed below:</div><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>Attributes<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>value<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>description</td></tr><tr><td>Class<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Classname<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>The class name of the specified element (classname)</td></tr><tr><td>Id<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Id<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">The unique id of the specified element</span></td></tr><tr><td>Style<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Style_definition<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">Specify the inline style of the element</span></td></tr><tr><td>Title<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Text<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>Additional information for the specified element (can be displayed in the tooltip)</td></tr></tbody></table><div>For more information on standard properties, please visit:</div><div><br></div><div>HTML Standard Attributes Reference Manual</div>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML attributes | jquerylearn.com', ' HTML tags can have attributes. Attributes provide more information about HTML elements.  Attributes always appear as name/value pairs, such as: name=\"value\".  Attributes are always specified in the start tag of the HTML element. ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(70, 7, 'html-title', 'HTML title paragraph', '		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  <h1>HTML title paragraph</h1><h2>HTML title</h2><div>In a HTML document, the title is important.</div><div><br></div><div>Heading is defined by tags such as &lt;h1&gt; - &lt;h6&gt;.</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;h1&gt; defines the largest title. &lt;h6&gt; defines the smallest title.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance&nbsp;</b></div>\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code  \" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 519px; height: 325px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;   \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;   \n&lt;head&gt;   \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;   \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;   \n&lt;/head&gt;  \n&lt;body&gt; \n&lt;h1&gt;this is the title 1&lt;/h1&gt;   \n&lt;h2&gt;this is the title 2&lt;/h2&gt;   \n&lt;h3&gt;this is the title 3&lt;/h3&gt;   \n&lt;h4&gt;this is the title 4&lt;/h4&gt;   \n&lt;h5&gt;this is the title 5&lt;/h5&gt;   \n&lt;h6&gt;this is the title 6&lt;/h6&gt;   \n&lt;/body&gt;   \n&lt;/html&gt;    \n	 </textarea>\n </form><div><b>Note </b>: The browser automatically adds a blank line before and after the title.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Note </b>: By default, HTML automatically adds an extra blank line before and after the block-level element, such as before and after the paragraph and title elements.</div><div><br></div><h2>The title is important</h2><div>Make sure to use the HTML heading tag only for the title. Don\'t just use the title to produce bold or large text.</div><div><br></div><div>Search engines use headings to index the structure and content of your web pages.</div><div><br></div><div>coz users can quickly navigate through your pages with headlines, it\'s important to use title to present the structure of the document.</div><div><br></div><div>H1 should be used as the main heading (most important), followed by h2 (secondary), followed by h3, and so on.</div><div><br></div><h2>HTML horizontal line</h2><div>The &lt;hr /&gt; tag creates a horizontal line in the HTML page.</div><div><br></div><div>The hr element can be used to separate content.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div>The following code will output the title and horizontal lines</div>\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 394px; height: 308px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;   \n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;   \n &lt;head&gt;   \n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;   \n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;   \n &lt;/head&gt;   \n &lt;body&gt;   \n    \n &lt;h1&gt;this is the first title&lt;/h1&gt;   \n &lt;hr/&gt;   \n &lt;h2&gt;this is the second title&lt;/h2&gt;   \n &lt;hr/&gt;   \n &lt;/body&gt;   \n &lt;/html&gt;   \n	 </textarea>\n </form><br><div>The above code outputs the &lt;h1&gt; header and the &lt;h6&gt; header, as well as two horizontal lines.<br><br></div><h2><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\">HTML paragraph</span></h2><div>Paragraphs are defined by the &lt;p&gt; tag.</div><div><br></div><div>See the example directly</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div>\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 404px; height: 260px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;   \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;   \n&lt;head&gt;   \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;   \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;   \n&lt;/head&gt;   \n&lt;body&gt;   \n&lt;p&gt;this is the first paragraph. &lt;/p&gt;   \n&lt;p&gt;this is the second paragraph. &lt;/p&gt;   \n&lt;/body&gt;   \n&lt;/html&gt;  \n	 </textarea>\n </form><pre><b>Program running result:</b><br>this is the first paragraph.<br>this is the second paragraph.</pre><div><br></div><div><b>Note </b>: The browser automatically adds a blank line before and after the paragraph. (&lt;p&gt; is a block-level element)</div><div><br></div><div><b>Tip </b>: Using an empty paragraph mark &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; to insert a blank line is a bad habit. Replace it with a &lt;br /&gt; tag! (But don\'t use the &lt;br /&gt; tag to create a list. Don\'t worry, you\'ll learn about HTML lists later.)<br><br></div><div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\">Don\'t forget to end the label</span></div><div>Even if you forget to use the end tag, most browsers will display the HTML correctly, like this:</div><br>\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 370px; height: 241px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;   \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;   \n&lt;head&gt;   \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;   \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;   \n&lt;/head&gt;   \n&lt;body&gt;   \n&lt;p&gt;Forgot the end tag   \n&lt;p&gt;Forgot the end tag   \n&lt;/body&gt;   \n&lt;/html&gt;\n	 </textarea>\n </form>\n<pre><b>Program running result:</b><br>Forgot the end tag<br>Forgot the end tag &nbsp; &nbsp;</pre><div><br></div><div>The above example is fine in most browsers, but don\'t rely on it. Forgetting to use the end tag can produce unexpected results and errors.</div><div><br></div><div>Note : End tags are not allowed in future HTML versions.</div><div><br></div><div>Tip : Closing HTML by closing tags is a way to write HTML that will stand the test of the future. Clearly marking where an element starts and ends where it makes the code easier to understand, both for you and for the browser.</div><div><br></div><h2>HTML wrap</h2><div>If you want to wrap (new line) without generating a new paragraph, use the &lt;br /&gt; tag</div><div><br></div><div>The &lt;br /&gt; element is an empty HTML element. Since closing a tag doesn\'t make sense, it doesn\'t end the tag.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div>\n<form method=\"post\" action=\"../lab\">\n	<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 389px; height: 294px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;   \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;   \n&lt;head&gt;   \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;   \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;   \n&lt;/head&gt;   \n&lt;body&gt;   \n&lt;p&gt;   \n    If  you &lt;br&gt; requires a  &lt;br&gt; newline &lt;br&gt;  paragraph, &lt;br&gt;  use the br tag.   \n&lt;/p&gt;   \n&lt;/body&gt;   \n&lt;/html&gt;   \n	 </textarea>\n </form><pre>Program running result:<br>If you&nbsp;<br>requires a<br>newline &nbsp;<br>paragraph,&nbsp;<br>use the br tag.&nbsp;</pre><div><br></div>\n\n\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML title paragraph |jquerylearn.com', ' In a HTML document, the title is important.  Heading is defined by tags such as <h1> - <h6>.  <h1> defines the largest title. <h6> defines the smallest title. ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(71, 7, 'html-style', 'HTML style', '		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  <h1>HTML style</h1><div>This section introduces HTML style style tags.</div><div><br></div><div>Let\'s look at a piece of code first.&nbsp;</div>\n<br>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; height: 307px; width: 417px;\"> \n  &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n &lt;head&gt; \n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n &lt;/head&gt; \n &lt;div style=\"background-color:black;\"&gt; \n  \n &lt;h1 style=\"color: white\"&gt;the color of the title&lt;/h1&gt; \n  \n &lt;p style=\"color:red\"&gt; \n     me is the color of the label&lt;/p&gt; \n &lt;/div&gt; \n &lt;/html&gt; \n</textarea></form>\n<br>\n<div>The above code means to change the background color of the webpage to black, the text color of the title to white, and the text of the paragraph to red.</div><div><br></div><div><div>You can see that the above code, whether it is the label &lt;body&gt;, &lt;h1&gt; or &lt;p&gt;, has a style in their label. Now we know that the style attribute is used to change the style of the HTML element.</div></div><h2>HTML style attribute</h2><div><b>the role of the tyle attribute </b>: provides a general way to change the style of all HTML elements.</div><div><br></div><div>Styles were introduced in HTML 4 and are a new and preferred way to change the style of HTML elements. Wif HTML styles, you can add styles directly to HTML elements by using the style attribute, or indirectly in a separate style sheet (CSS file).</div><div><br></div><div><b>You can learn all about styles and CSS in our CSS tutorials.</b></div><div><br></div><div>In our HTML tutorial, we\'ll use the style attribute to explain the HTML style to you.</div><div><br></div><div><div><b>Deprecated labels and attributes</b></div><div><br></div><div>In HTML 4, there are several tags and attributes that are obsolete. Deprecated means that these tags and attributes will not be supported in future versions of HTML and XHTML.</div><div><br></div><div>The message here is clear: please avoid using these discarded tags and attributes!</div><div><br></div><div>The following tags and attributes should be avoided:</div></div><br><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><b>label</b></td><td><b>Attributes</b></td></tr><tr><td>&lt;center&gt;</td><td>Define the content that &nbsp;is centered.<br></td></tr>\n\n<tr>\n<td>&lt;font&gt; and &lt;basefont&gt;</td>\n<td>Define HTML fonts.</td>\n</tr><tr><td>&lt;s&gt; and &lt;strike&gt;</td><td>Define strike through&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;u&gt;</td><td>Define underlined text</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp; <b>Attributes</b></td><td><b>description</b></td></tr><tr><td>Align</td><td>Define the alignment of the text</td></tr><tr><td>Bgcolor</td><td>Define background color</td></tr><tr><td>Color</td><td>Define text color</td></tr></tbody></table><div>For these tags and attributes: use style instead!</div><div><br></div><h2>HTML style instance - background color</h2><div><br></div><div>the background-color property defines the background color for the element:</div>\n<br>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 385px; height: 260px;\"> \n &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n &lt;head&gt; \n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n &lt;/head&gt; \n &lt;body style=\"background-color:yellow\"&gt; \n  \n &lt;/body&gt; \n &lt;/html&gt; \n \n\n</textarea></form>\n<br>\n<div>The style attribute eliminates the \"old\" bgcolor attribute.</div>\n<br>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 353px; height: 224px;\"> \n &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n &lt;head&gt; \n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n &lt;/head&gt; \n &lt;div bgcolor=\"yellow\"&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;dis is text&lt;/p&gt; \n &lt;/div&gt; \n &lt;/html&gt; \n\n</textarea></form><h2>HTML style instance - font, color, and size</h2><div>The font-family, color, and font-size properties define the font family, color, and font size of the text in the element, respectively:</div>\n<br>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 297px; height: 284px;\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n &lt;head&gt;\n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n &lt;/head&gt;\n \n &lt;h1 style=\"font-family:verdana\"&gt;Title&lt;/h1&gt;\n &lt;p style=\"font-family:arial;color:red;font-size:20px;\"&gt;paragraph&lt;/p&gt;\n \n &lt;/body&gt;\n &lt;/html&gt;\n</textarea></form>\n<div>The style attribute eliminates the old &lt;font&gt; tag and is no longer usable.</div>\n<br>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 319px; height: 324px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n &lt;head&gt;\n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n &lt;/head&gt;\n \n &lt;h1&gt;&lt;font face=\"verdana\"&gt;Title&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;\n &lt;p&gt;&lt;font size=\"5\" face=\"arial\" color=\"red\"&gt;Paragraph&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n \n &lt;/body&gt;\n &lt;/html&gt;\n</textarea></form>\n<br>\n<h2>HTML style instance - text alignment</h2><div><br></div><div>The text-align attribute specifies the horizontal alignment of the text in the element:</div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 444px; height: 220px;\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n &lt;head&gt; \n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n &lt;/head&gt; \n  &lt;body&gt; \n &lt;h1 style=\"font-family:verdana\"&gt;Title&lt;/h1&gt; \n &lt;p style=\"font-family:arial;color:red;font-size:20px;\"&gt;paragraph&lt;/p&gt; \n  \n &lt;/body&gt; \n &lt;/html&gt; \n\n</textarea></form>\n<br>\n<div>The style attribute eliminates the old \"align\" attribute.</div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 503px; height: 148px;\"> \n \n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n &lt;head&gt; \n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n &lt;/head&gt; \n &lt;body&gt; \n &lt;h1 align=\"center\"&gt;Title&lt;/h1&gt; \n  \n &lt;p&gt;the headings above are centered on the page. the headings above are centered on the page. the headings above are centered on the page. &lt;/p&gt; \n &lt;/body&gt; \n &lt;/html&gt; \n\n</textarea>	\n</form>	  		   <br><br>\n		   <br><br>\n		   <br>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML style | jquerylearn.com', '  You can see that the above code, whether it is the label <body>, <h1> or <p>, has a style in their label. Now we know that the style attribute is used to change the style of the    ', '2018-08-23 14:24:10', 'akshay'),
(72, 7, 'html-common-text-format', ' Html common text format', '		  		  		  		  		  		  <h1>Html common text format</h1><div>HTML defines tags in text format, such as using them to make fonts bold or italic.</div><div><br></div><div>Here are some common text formatting tags</div><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><b>label<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></b></td><td><b>description</b></td></tr><tr><td>&lt;b&gt;</td><td>Define bold text.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;big&gt;</td><td>Define a large word.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;em&gt;</td><td>Define emphasis on text.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;i&gt;</td><td>Define italics.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;small&gt;</td><td>Define a small word.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;</td><td>&nbsp;Define aggravated tone.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;sub&gt;</td><td>Define the subscript.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;sup&gt;</td><td>Define the upper label.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;ins&gt;</td><td>Define the insertion word.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;del&gt;</td><td>Define the delete word.</td></tr></tbody></table><div><br></div><h2>Computer Output tab</h2><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><b>label<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></b></td><td><b>description</b></td></tr><tr><td>&lt;code&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define the computer code.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;kbd&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define the keyboard code.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;samp&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define a computer code sample.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;tt&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define the typewriter code.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;var&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define variables.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;pre&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define pre-formatted text</td></tr></tbody></table><div><br>In the following sections, we will introduce computer code elements.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>The following example uses some of the above tags, you can compare the results of the HTML display.</div>\n<br>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 364px; height: 205px;\"> \n &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Bold is represented by b. &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt; Italics are indicated by i. &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;&lt;del&gt;Shrimp sister &lt;/del&gt; in the word line indicates deletion. &lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;&lt;ins&gt;Sing to sing and sing&lt;/ins&gt; is inserted underlined. &lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;X&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; where 2 is the subscript&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;X&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; 2 of which is the superscript&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt; Study hard and go up every day. Indentation of this sentence means reference &lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;pre&gt; \nthis is \nPreformatted text. \nThe text in the pre tag is reserved \nSpace and \nBranch. \n&lt;/pre&gt; \n&lt;code&gt;call getOrders&lt;/code&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;Use the code to display the computer code. The characters displayed in the code are monospaced characters. &lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n \n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<div><br></div><div><b>References, citations, and term definitions</b></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>label<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td><b>description</b></td></tr><tr><td>&lt;abbr&gt;</td><td>&nbsp;Define an abbreviation</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;acronym&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define an acronym.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;address&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define the address.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;bdo&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define the text direction.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;blockquote&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>Define long references.</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp; &lt;q&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define short quotations.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;cite&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define references, citations.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;dfn&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define a definition project.</td></tr></tbody></table><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>HTML &lt;q&gt; for short references</div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n &lt;head&gt; \n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n &lt;/head&gt; \n &lt;body&gt;   \n &lt;p&gt;Browseres usually enclose quotes around the q element. &lt;/p&gt;   \n &lt;p&gt;The goal of mankind is to &lt;q&gt;build a world where people live in harmony with nature. &lt;/q&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   \n &lt;/body&gt; \n &lt;/html&gt; \n \n\n</textarea></form>\n<div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div>HTML &lt;blockquote&gt; for long references</div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;The browser usually indents the blockquote element. &lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;blockquote cite=\" \"&gt; \n    For 50 years, WWF has been committed to protecting the future of nature. \n WWF works in 100 countries and is supported by 1.2 million members in the US and nearly 5 million members worldwide. \n&lt;/blockquote&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n \n</textarea></form>\n<div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>The HTML &lt;abbr&gt; element defines an abbreviation or an acronym.</div><div><br></div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 264px; height: 106px;\"> \n \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;&lt;abbr title=\"Teh People\'s Republic of China\"&gt;PRC&lt;/abbr&gt; was founded in 1949. &lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;Marking abbreviations provides useful information for browsers, translation systems, and search engines. &lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n \n</textarea></form>\n<div><b>Program running result:</b></div><div><br></div><div>PRC was established in 1949.</div><div><br></div><div>Marking abbreviations provides useful information for browsers, translation systems, and search engines.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>The HTML &lt;bdo&gt; element defines a bi-directional override.</div><div><br></div><div>If your browser supports bdo, the text will be written from right to left (rtl):</div><div><br></div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 533px; height: 429px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n &lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n &lt;head&gt; \n     &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n     &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n &lt;/head&gt; \n &lt;body&gt; \n  \n &lt;p&gt; \n     If your browser supports bdo, the text will be written from right to left (rtl): \n &lt;/p&gt; \n  \n &lt;bdo dir=\"rtl\"&gt; \n     Dis line will be written from right to left \n &lt;/bdo&gt; \n  \n &lt;/body&gt; \n &lt;/html&gt; \n</textarea></form>\n<div>&nbsp;</div><div>These tags are used in the same way. If you are interested, you can try it.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>How to see the source code of HTML</div><div><br></div><div>The HTML page that is seen in the browser is the result of the browser interpreting the HTML source code.</div><div><br></div><div>There are two ways to view the source code of this HTML. One is to click the right mouse button and click the View Source command; the second is to select the Source command in the browser menu View.</div><div><br></div><div>Use View Source to get the source code of the webpage, so you can learn from other people\'s well-written places. However, if you have little knowledge of HTML, looking at other people\'s complex HTML source code will only make you dizzy. I suggest you wait a second time and learn some basics.</div><div><br></div>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'Html common text format', ' HTML defines tags in text format, such as using them to make fonts bold or italic.Here are some common text formatting tags: ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(73, 7, 'html-computer-code', 'HTML computer code', '		  		  		  		  		  		  <h1>HTML computer code</h1><div>Computer code refers to the way the computer internally represents letters or numbers.</div><div><br></div><div>In general, HTML uses variable letter sizes, as well as variable letter spacing.</div><div><br></div><div>This is not required when the computer code example is displayed.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Computer code element</b></div><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>label<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>description</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;code&gt;</td><td>Defining computer code text</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;kbd&gt;<span class=\"Apple-tab-span\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>Define keyboard text</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;samp&gt;</td><td>Define computer code examples</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;var&gt;</td><td>Defining variables</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;pre&gt;</td><td>Defining preformatted text</td></tr></tbody></table><h2>The HTML &lt;kbd&gt; element defines keyboard input:</h2><div><b>Instance</b></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body style=\"font-size:16px\"&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;The HTML kbd element represents keyboard input:&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;&lt;kbd&gt;File | Open...&lt;/kbd&gt;&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<br>\n<br>\n<div>You can remove the &lt;kbd&gt; from the above code to see what is different.</div><div><br></div><h2>The HTML &lt;samp&gt; element defines the computer output:</h2><div><b>Instance</b></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; height: 170px; width: 300px;\">&lt;br /&gt;\n \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body style=\"font-size:16px\"&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;The HTML samp element represents an example of computer output:&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;samp&gt; \n    Demo.example.com login: Apr 12 09:10:17 \n    Linux 2.6.10-grsec+gg3+e+fhs6b+nfs+gr0501+++p3+c4a+gr2b-reslog-v6.189 \n&lt;/samp&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n \n\n</textarea>\n</form><br>\n<br>\n<div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\">HTML &lt;code&gt; element definition programming:</span></div><div><br></div><div>The &lt;code&gt; element does not retain extra spaces and lines:</div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\"> \n \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body style=\"font-size:16px\"&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;code example&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;code&gt; \n    Var person = { \n    firstName: \"Bill\", \n    lastName: \"Gates\", \n    Age: 50, \n    eyeColor:\"blue\" \n    } \n&lt;/code&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n \n\n</textarea>\n</form><br>\n<br>\n<div><b>Program running result:</b></div>\n<br>\n<pre><b>Code example</b><br>&nbsp; &nbsp;Var person = { firstName:\"Bill\", lastName:\"Gates\", age:50, eyeColor:\"blue\" }&nbsp;</pre><div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\"><br>HTML &lt;pre&gt; element</span></div><div><b>Instance</b></div>\n<br>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 639px; height: 182px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body style=\"font-size:16px\"&gt; \nThe &lt;p&gt;code element does not preserve extra spaces and lines:&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;To resolve this issue, you must enclose the code in the pre element:&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;code&gt; \n&lt;pre&gt; \nVar person = { \n    firstName: \"Bill\", \n    lastName: \"Gates\", \n    Age: 50, \n    eyeColor:\"blue\" \n} \n&lt;/pre&gt; \n&lt;/code&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt; \n\n</textarea>\n</form><br><div><br></div><div>The HTML &lt;var&gt; element defines a mathematical variable:</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code execute\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; \n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt; \n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt; \n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt; \n&lt;body style=\"font-size:16px\"&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;Einstein\'s formula:&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;p&gt;&lt;var&gt;E&lt;/var&gt; = &lt;var&gt;m&lt;/var&gt; &lt;var&gt;c&lt;/var&gt;&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt; \n&lt;/body&gt; \n&lt;/html&gt;  \n</textarea>	\n</form> \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML computer code | jquerylearn.com', ' Computer code refers to the way the computer internally represents letters or numbers.  In general, HTML uses variable letter sizes, as well as variable letter spacing.  This is not required when the computer code example is displayed.  ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay');
