(74, 7, 'html-css', 'HTML CSS', '		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		   <h1>HTML CSS</h1><div>CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) A style used to render HTML element tags. For example, we learned to add a background color to &lt;body&gt;. Change the color of the text in the &lt;p&gt; tag, these are done with css</div><div><br></div><h2>How to use CSS</h2><div>CSS was originally introduced in HTML 4 and was introduced for better rendering of HTML elements.</div><div><br></div><div><b>CSS can be added to HTML in the following ways:</b></div><div><br></div><div><b>Inline style</b> - use the \"style\" attribute in the HTML element</div><div><br></div><div><b>Internal style sheet</b> - use the &lt;style&gt; element in the &lt;head&gt; section of the HTML document to include CSS</div><div><br></div><div><b>External references</b> - use external CSS files</div><div><br></div><div>The best way is to externally reference CSS files. CSS files refer to files ending in .css. Our html files end in .html.</div><div><br></div><div>In our HTML tutorial, we used inline CSS styles to introduce examples, which is a simplified example and makes it easier to edit code online and run instances online.</div><div><br></div><div>You can learn more about CSS through the CSS tutorial CSS tutorial on this site.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><h2>Inline style</h2><div><br></div><div>Inline styles are defined directly inside the HTML tags using the style attribute. We also mentioned the previous lessons. See the example below.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 385px; height: 357px;\"> \n\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;p style=\"color: red; margin-left: 20px\"&gt;\n    I am inline style\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea> \n</form>\n\n<div>The css style above turns the text in the &lt;p&gt; tag black, then the text moves 20px to the left, and px refers to the pixel.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><h2>Internal style sheet</h2><div>When a single file requires special styles, such as setting the two &lt;P&gt; tags to red, if you define them with inline styles, you need to write the css style on both &lt;P&gt; tags, if it is 5, 10&lt;P &gt; Labels, is it very troublesome, this is the use of our internal style sheet. You can define an internal style sheet in the &lt;head&gt; section via the &lt;style&gt; tag, like this:</div><div><br></div>\n<form>\n<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; height: 284px; width: 795px;\"> \n\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n    &lt;style type=\"text/css\"&gt;\n        p{color: red}\n    &lt;/style&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\n    My color is defined in the head tag\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\n    My color is defined in the head tag\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\n    My color is defined in the head tag\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea> \n</form>\n<div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\">External style sheet</span></div><div>An external style sheet is the ideal choice when styles need to be applied to many pages.</div><div><br></div><div>External style sheets are introduced into an external css file using the &lt;link&gt; tag. With an external style sheet, you can change the appearance of the entire site by changing a file.</div><div><br></div><div>For example, a css file defines that the background color of &lt;body&gt; turns yellow, the &lt;h1&gt; title turns red, &lt;p&gt; turns blue, and the css file is as follows</div><div><br></div><div>Body{background-color:yellow;}</div><div>p{color: blue;}</div><div>H1{color: red;}</div><div>Introducing css files with &lt;link&gt; in HTML files</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 814px; height: 265px;\">   &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n    &lt;link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"first.css\"&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;h1&gt;External style sheet&lt;/h1&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\n    My color is defined by an external style sheet\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\n    My color is defined by an external style sheet\n&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n</textarea> \n</form>\n\n<h2><br>HTML style tags</h2><div><br></div><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>label<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>description</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;style&gt;</td><td>Define text style</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;link&gt;</td><td>Define resource reference address</td></tr></tbody></table><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>The &lt;a&gt; link label we learned earlier, below is underlined, we use the css style to remove the underline</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; height: 203px; width: 837px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"http://www.jquerylearn.com/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\"&gt;Visit jquerylearn.com!&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n</textarea> \n</form>\n<div>\n		   \n		   \n		  </div> \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML CSS | jquerylearn.com', '  CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) A style used to render HTML element tags. For example, we learned to add a background color to <body>. Change the color of the text in the <p> tag, these are done with css  ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(75, 7, 'html-link', 'HTML link', '		  		  		  		  		  		  		   <h1>HTML link</h1><div>HTML uses hyperlinks to connect to another document on the web.</div><div><br></div><div>Links can be found in almost all web pages. Click on a link to jump from one page to another.</div><div><br></div><div>Let\'s first look at a link instance</div><div><br></div>\n								   <form>\n								   <textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 532px; height: 321px;\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;php.cn&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=\"/\"&gt;PHP Chinese Network&lt;/a&gt; is a link to a page in this website. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://www.baidu.com/\"&gt;Baidu&lt;/a&gt; This is a link to Baidu&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n								</form>   \n								   <div><br></div><h2>HTML hyperlink (link)</h2><div><br></div><div>HTML uses the tag &lt;a&gt; to set up hypertext links.</div><div><br></div><div>A hyperlink can be a word, a word, or a group of words, or it can be an image that you can click to jump to a new document or a section of the current document.</div><div><br></div><div>When you move the mouse pointer over a link in a web page, the arrow turns into a small hand.</div><div><br></div><div>The href attribute is used in the tag &lt;a&gt; to describe the address of the link.</div><div><br></div><div>For example, if you link to the php.cn site home page, you can say this:</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;a href=\"http://www.php.cn\"&gt;PHP Chinese Network&lt;/a&gt;&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>By default, links will appear in the browser in the following form:</b></div><div><br></div><div><b>An non-visited link</b> appears as a blue font with an underscore.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Visited links</b> appear purple and underlined.</div><div><br></div><div><b>When you click on a link </b>, the link appears red and underlined.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Note </b>: If CSS styles are set for these hyperlinks, the presentation style will be displayed according to the CSS settings.</div><div><br></div><h2>HTML connection - id attribute</h2><div><br></div><div>The id attribute can be used to create bookmark tags in an HTML document.</div><div><br></div><div>Hint: Bookmarks are not displayed in any special way, are not displayed in HTML documents, so they are hidden from the reader.</div><div><br></div><div>Insert an ID in the HTML document:</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;a id=\"tips\"&gt;Useful tips section&lt;/a&gt;</div><div><br></div><div>Create a link in the HTML document to the \"useful hints section (id=\"tips\")\":</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;a href=\"#tips\"&gt;Access the helpful tips section&lt;/a&gt;</div><div><br></div><div>Or, create a link from another page to the \"useful hints section (id=\"tips\")\":</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;a href=\"http://www.php.cn/html/html-links.html#tips\"&gt;</div><div>Access the helpful tips section&lt;/a&gt;</div><div><br></div><h2>Basic considerations&nbsp;</h2><div><br></div><div>Note: Always add a forward slash to the subfolder. If you write the link like this: href=\"http://www.php.cn/html\", it will generate two HTTP requests to the server. This is because the server adds a forward slash to this address and then creates a new request like this: href=\"http://www.php.cn/html/\".</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>How to use image links.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 834px; height: 371px;\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;php.cn&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Create an image link:\n    &lt;a href=\"http://www.php.cn/\"&gt;\n        &lt;img src=\"1.jpg\" alt=\"HTML Tutorial\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Borderless image links:\n    &lt;a href=\"http://www.php.cn/html/\"&gt;\n        &lt;img border=\"0\" src=\"1.jpg\" alt=\"HTML tutorial\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n<div>The image uses the &lt;img&gt; tag, which will be discussed later.</div><div><br></div><div>Click on the image above will jump to http://www.php.cn/ this URL</div>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML links | jquerylearn.com', '  HTML uses hyperlinks to connect to another document on the web.  Links can be found in almost all web pages. Click on a link to jump from one page to another.  ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(76, 7, 'html-image', 'HTML image', '		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		  		   <h2>HTML image&nbsp;</h2><div><br></div><h2>HTML image - image tag ( &lt;img&gt;)</h2><div><br></div><div><div>In HTML, images are defined by &lt;img&gt; tags.</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;img&gt; is an empty tag, meaning that it only contains attributes and their are no closed tags.</div></div><div><br></div><h2>HTML image - source attribute (Src)</h2><div><br></div><div><div>To display an image on a page, you need to use teh source attribute (src). Src means \"source\". Refers to teh location where teh image is stored.</div><div><br></div><div>If teh image and HTML text are in teh same directory: for example index.html and img.jpg</div><div><br></div><div>Written: &lt;img src=\"img.jpg\"&gt;</div><div><br></div><div>Images and HTML are not in teh same directory: their are two cases:</div><div><br></div><div>1, teh picture img.jpg in teh folder images, index.html and images folder in teh same directory</div><div><br></div><div>Written by: &lt;img src=\"images/img.jpg\"&gt;</div><div><br></div><div>2, teh picture img.jpg in teh folder images, index.html in teh controller folder, images and controller folder in teh same directory</div><div><br></div><div>Written by: &lt;img src=\"../images/img.jpg\"&gt;</div><div><br></div><div>If teh source is from teh Internet, you must use an absolute path.</div><div><br></div><div>Written by: &lt;img src=\"http://www.baidu.com/pic/img.jpg\"&gt;</div></div><div><br></div><h2>HTML image - Alt attribute</h2><div><br></div><div><div>Teh alt attribute is used to define a string of prepared replaceable text for teh image.</div><div><br></div><div>Teh value of teh replacement text attribute is user-defined.</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;img src=\"1.jpg\" alt=\"Show when teh image does not show up\"&gt;</div><div><br></div><div>When teh browser is unable to load teh image, teh replacement text attribute tells teh reader wat information they have lost. At this point, teh browser will display this alternative text instead of teh image. It’s a good practice to add alternate text attributes to teh images on teh page.</div><div><br></div><div>It helps to display information better and is very useful for those who use a plain text browser.</div></div><div><br></div><h2>HTML image - set teh height and width of teh image</h2><div><br></div><div><div>Teh height and width properties are used to set teh height and width of teh image.</div><div><br></div><div>Teh default value of teh attribute value is pixels:</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;img src=\"../style/images/pulpit.jpg\" alt=\"Pulpit rock\" width=\"304\" height=\"228\"&gt;</div><div><br></div><div><b>Tip</b> : A good habit of specifying teh height and width of teh image. If teh image specifies a height width, teh specified size is preserved when teh page loads. If you do not specify teh size of teh image, loading teh page may damage teh overall layout of teh HTML page.</div></div><div><br></div><h2>Basic considerations&nbsp;</h2><div><b>Note </b>: If an HTML file contains ten images, tan 11 files need to be loaded in order to display this page correctly. Loading images takes time, so our advice is: use images wif caution.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Note </b>: When loading teh page, pay attention to teh path of teh inserted page image. If teh position of teh image cannot be set correctly, teh browser cannot load teh image, and teh image label will display a broken image.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Add a background image to our web page</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n   <textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 532px; height: 321px;\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;php.cn&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;div style=\"background:url(\'https://jquerylearn.com/uploads/photo_15317521361.jpeg\')\"&gt;;\n&lt;h3&gt;Image background&lt;/h3&gt;\nBoth &lt;p&gt;gif and jpg files can be used as HTML backgrounds. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;If teh image is smaller than teh page, teh image will be repeated. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<div>You run teh program to see if their is any change.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>This example demonstrates how to adjust teh picture to a different size.</div>\n \n<form>\n   <textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 532px; height: 321px;\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;php.cn&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;img src=\"https://jquerylearn.com/uploads/photo_15317521361.jpeg\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\"&gt;\n&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;img src=\"https://jquerylearn.com/uploads/photo_15317521361.jpeg\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\"&gt;\n&lt;br /&gt;\n&lt;img src=\"https://jquerylearn.com/uploads/photo_15317521361.jpeg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\"&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;You can zoom in or out by changing teh values ​​of teh \"height\" and \"width\" properties of teh img tag. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n\n<div>Run teh program to see</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Make a hyperlink wif a picture</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n								   <textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 532px; height: 321px;\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;php.cn&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Create an image link:\n    &lt;a href=\"http://www.php.cn/\"&gt;\n        &lt;img src=\"https://jquerylearn.com/uploads/photo_15317521361.jpeg\" alt=\"HTML Tutorial\" width=\"100\" height=\"100\"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n\n<div>Run teh program and click on teh image to see</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div>This example shows how to set a normal image as an image map.</div>\n<form>\n   <textarea name=\"data\" class=\"code execute\" style=\"margin: 0px; width: 532px; height: 321px;\"> \n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Please move the mouse over the image to see how the coordinates of the status bar change. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;a href=\"\"&gt;\n    &lt;img src=\"http://p11.qhimg.com/t010fae31f5653bffe7.jpg\" ismap /&gt;\n&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n\n<div>Run and see</div><div><br></div><div>HTML image tag</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><b>Label<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></b><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\"><b>&nbsp; </b>&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td><b>Description</b></td></tr><tr><td>&lt;img&gt;</td><td>Define teh image.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;map&gt;</td><td>Define an image map.</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;area&gt;</td><td>Define a clickable area in teh image map.</td></tr></tbody></table><div><div>Find a picture and put it in your designated directory, try to insert it into your web page.</div></div><div><br></div><br>\n		   <br>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML image - image tag ( <img>)', ' In HTML, images are defined by <img> tags.  <img> is an empty tag, meaning that it only contains attributes and there are no closed tags. ', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(77, 7, 'html-table', 'HTML table', '		  		  		  		  		  		   <h1>HTML form</h1><div>Forms are very common in our daily lives, but how do we output the forms on our web pages?</div><div><br></div><div>The &lt;table&gt; tag defines an HTML table.</div><div><br></div><div><b>A simple</b> HTML table consists of a table element and one or more tr, th, or td elements.</div><div><br></div><div>The tr element defines the table row, the th element defines the header, and the td element defines the table cell.</div><div><br></div><div>Let\'s make the simplest form</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"10\"&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;January&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;¥100&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;February&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;¥200&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>Cellspacing </b>, the distance between cells</div><div><br></div><div><b>Cellpadding </b>, the distance between the text and the cell border is in pixels</div><div><br></div><div><b>border</b>&nbsp; to add text border border table border = 0 set to not display the border</div><div><br></div><div>The above three attribute values ​​can be set by themselves, set according to their own requirements.</div><div><br></div><h2>HTML table header</h2><div>The header of the table is defined using the &lt;th&gt; tag.</div><div><br></div><div>Most browsers will display the header as bold text centered:</div><div><br></div><div>Instance</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"10\"&gt;\n    &lt;th&gt;month&lt;/th&gt;\n    &lt;th&gt;Amount&lt;/th&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;January&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;¥100&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;February&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;¥200&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><h2>Colspan and rowspan</h2><div>You can merge cells in landscape and portrait by adding two attributes, colspan and rowspan, to the &lt;td&gt; tag.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Before the merger</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"20\"&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div>After the merger</div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"20\"&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td colspan=\"2\"&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td rowspan=\"2\"&gt;cells&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td rowspan=\"2\"&gt;cells&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;cell&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div>Look for the law</div><h2>More examples</h2><div>This example demonstrates a table without a border.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html lang=\"en\"&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;This table has no borders:&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;table&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;200&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;300&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;500&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;600&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;This table has no borders:&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;table border=\"0\"&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;200&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;300&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;500&lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;600&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>This example demonstrates how to display elements within different elements.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;table border=\"1\"&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;\n            &lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph&lt;/p&gt;\n            &lt;p&gt;This is another paragraph&lt;/p&gt;\n        &lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;This cell contains a table:\n            &lt;table border=\"1\"&gt;\n                &lt;tr&gt;\n                    &lt;td&gt;A&lt;/td&gt;\n                    &lt;td&gt;B&lt;/td&gt;\n                &lt;/tr&gt;\n                &lt;tr&gt;\n                    &lt;td&gt;C&lt;/td&gt;\n                    &lt;td&gt;D&lt;/td&gt;\n                &lt;/tr&gt;\n            &lt;/table&gt;\n        &lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n    &lt;tr&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;This cell contains a list\n            &lt;ul&gt;\n                &lt;li&gt;apples&lt;/li&gt;\n                &lt;li&gt;bananas&lt;/li&gt;\n                &lt;li&gt;pineapples&lt;/li&gt;\n            &lt;/ul&gt;\n        &lt;/td&gt;\n        &lt;td&gt;HELLO&lt;/td&gt;\n    &lt;/tr&gt;\n&lt;/table&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><h2>HTML table label</h2><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>label<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>description</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;table&gt;</td><td>Definition form</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;th&gt;</td><td>Define the header of the table</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;tr&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>Define the row of the table</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;td&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>Defining table cells</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;caption&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define table title</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;colgroup&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define the group of table columns</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;col&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define attributes for table columns</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;thead&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Define the header of the table</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;tbody&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></td><td>Defining the body of the form</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;tfoot&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>Define the footer of the table</td></tr></tbody></table><div><br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><br>\n		   <br>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML table | jquerylearn.com', 'Forms are very common in our daily lives, but how do we output the forms on our web pages?\nThe <table> tag defines an HTML table.\nA simple HTML table consists of a table element and one or more tr, th, or td elements.\nThe tr element defines the table row, the th element defines the header, and the td element defines the table cell.', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(78, 7, 'html-list', 'HTML list', '		  		  		  		  		   <h1>HTML list</h1><div><b>HTML supports ordered, unordered, and defined lists:</b></div><div><br></div><h2>Ordered list</h2><div><br></div><div>The ordered list begins with the &lt;ol&gt; tag. Each list item begins with the &lt;li&gt; tag.</div><div><br></div><div>List item items are marked with numbers.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>This example demonstrates an ordered list.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;ol&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Coffee&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Tea&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Milk&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;\n&lt;ol start=\"50\"&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Coffee&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Tea&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Milk&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ol&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><h2>HTML unordered list</h2><div><br></div><div>An unordered list is a list of items that are marked with bold dots (typically small black circles).</div><div><br></div><div>Unordered list using &lt;ul&gt; tag</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>This example demonstrates an unordered sequence table.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;An unordered list:&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;ul&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Coffee&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;tea&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;milk&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\">HTML custom list</span></div><div>A custom list is more than just a list of items, but a combination of items and their comments.</div><div><br></div><div>The custom list begins with a &lt;dl&gt; tag. Each custom list item begins with &lt;dt&gt;. The definition of each custom list item begins with &lt;dd&gt;.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>This example demonstrates a list of definitions.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;h2&gt;A list of definitions:&lt;/h2&gt;\n&lt;dl&gt;\n    &lt;dt&gt;computer&lt;/dt&gt;\n    &lt;dd&gt;The instrument used for calculation...&lt;/dd&gt;\n    &lt;dt&gt;display&lt;/dt&gt;\n    &lt;dd&gt;Device that visually displays information...&lt;/dd&gt;\n&lt;/dl&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div><b>Tip </b>: Paragraphs, line breaks, images, links, and other lists can be used inside a list item.</div><div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\">More examples</span></div><div>This example demonstrates different types of unordered lists.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;Disc bulleted list:&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;ul type=\"disc\"&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Apple&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Banana&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Lemon&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Orange&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;Circle bulleted list:&lt;/h4&gt;\n&lt;ul type=\"circle\"&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Apple&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Banana&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Lemon&lt;/li&gt;\n    &lt;li&gt;Orange&lt;/li&gt;\n&lt;/ul&gt;\n&lt;h4&gt;Square bulleted list:&lt;/h4&gt;