(81, 7, 'html-form', 'HTML form', '		  		  		  		  		   <h1>HTML form</h1><h2>What is a form</h2><div>The form is for collecting different types of user input, such as:</div><div><br></div><div>Website registration&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>log in&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Post resume</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Forum post</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Replies S voting, etc.</b></div><div><br></div><h2>HTML form</h2><div>A form is an area that contains form elements. A web page may have multiple forms, but a form corresponds to a form area, and only form items of the current form area can be submitted.</div><div><br></div><div>Form elements allow users to type in forms, such as textarea, drop-down lists, radio-buttons, checkboxes, and more.</div><div><br></div><div>The form is set using the form tag &lt;form&gt;:</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;form method=\"delivery method\" action=\"server file address\"&gt;</div><div><br></div><div>.input element</div><div><br></div><div>&lt;/form&gt;</div><div><br></div><div><b>Action is</b> used to configure where the form data is transferred, usually the address of a dynamic script, such as the address of a PHP file login.php&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>Method</b> can be GET or POST (if not set, the system defaults to GET, but in most cases we use POST, GET is submitted as a parameter, the user can directly see the submitted parameters, post is via HTTP post mechanism, will Each field in the form is placed in the HTML HEADER along with the content placed in the HTML HEADER. The user does not see the process.)</div><div><br><br></div><div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\">HTML form - input element</span></div><div>The form tag used in most cases is the input tag (&lt;input&gt;).</div><div><br></div><div>The input type is defined by the type attribute (type). The most common input types used are as follows:<br><br></div><h2>Text field</h2><div>The text field is set by the &lt;input type=\"text\"&gt; tag, and the text field is used when the user wants to type letters, numbers, etc. into the form.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form&gt;\n    Text field: &lt;input type=\"text\" name=\"firstname\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n    Text field: &lt;input type=\"text\" name=\"lastname\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<div><br></div><h2>Password field</h2><div>The password field is defined by the tag &lt;input type=\"password\"&gt;:</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form&gt;\n    Name: &lt;input type=\"text\" name=\"firstname\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n    Password: &lt;input type=\"password\" name=\"lastname\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div><b>Note</b> : Password field characters are not displayed in plain text, but instead are replaced with an asterisk or dot.</div><div><br></div><h2>Radio button</h2><div>&lt;input type=\"radio\"&gt; tag defines form radio button options</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"radio\" name=\"sex\" value=\"male\"&gt;Men&lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"radio\" name=\"sex\" value=\"female\"&gt;female\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><h2>Check box</h2><div>&lt;input type=\"checkbox\"&gt; A checkbox is defined. The user needs to select one or several options from several given choices.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"vehicle\" value=\"Bicycle\"&gt;Bicycle\n&lt;input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"vehicle\" value=\"car\"&gt;car\n&lt;input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"vehicle\" value=\"Aircraft\"&gt;Aircraft\n&lt;input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"vehicle\" value=\"ship\"ship\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><h2>Submit button</h2><div>&lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt; defines the submit button.</div><div><br></div><div>When the user clicks the confirmation button, the contents of the form are transferred to another file. The action attribute of the form defines the file name of the destination file. This file defined by the action attribute usually performs related processing on the received input data. :</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form name=\"input\" action=\"action.php\" method=\"post\"&gt;\n    Username &lt;input type=\"text\" name=\"user\"&gt;&lt;br/&gt;\n    Password &lt;input type=\"password\" name=\"user\"&gt;\n     &lt;input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div>If you type a few letters in the text box above and click the OK button, the input data will be sent to the \"action.php\" page as a post. This page will display the results of the input.</div><div><br></div><h2>HTML form tag</h2><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td>Label<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;form&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define a form for user input</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;input&gt;</td><td>Define input fields</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;textarea&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>Define a text field (a multi-line input control)</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;label&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>The label defining the &lt;input&gt; element, typically the input title</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;fieldset&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Defines a set of related form elements and includes them with a bounding box</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;legend&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Defines the title of the &lt;fieldset&gt; element</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;select&gt;</td><td>Defined a drop-down list of options</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;optgroup&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span></td><td>Define option groups</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;option&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define options in the drop-down list</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;button&gt;<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td><td>Define a click button</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;datalist&gt;</td><td>Specify a list of predefined input control options</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;keygen&gt;</td><td>The key pair generator field that defines the form</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;output&gt;</td><td>Define a calculation result</td></tr></tbody></table><div><br></div><div>To learn more about HTML form tags, please visit our HTML reference manual.</div><div><br></div><h2>More examples</h2><div>This example demonstrates how to create a simple drop-down list box in an HTML page. The drop-down list box is an optional list. A drop-down list with pre-selected values.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"\"&gt;\n    &lt;select name=\"degrees\"&gt;\n        &lt;option value=\"Primary School\"&gt;Primary School&lt;/option&gt;\n        &lt;option value=\"junior middle school\"&gt;junior high school&lt;/option&gt;\n        &lt;option value=\"College\" selected&gt;College&lt;/option&gt;\n        &lt;option value=\"undergraduate\"&gt;undergraduate&lt;/option&gt;\n        &lt;option value=\"Master\"&gt;Master&lt;/option&gt;\n        &lt;option value=\"Dr.\"&gt;PhD&lt;/option&gt;\n    &lt;/select&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div>This example demonstrates how to create a text field (multi-line text input control). Users can write text in the text field. The number of words that can be written to characters is unlimited , as well as a button. You can customize the text on the button.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"\"&gt;\n&lt;textarea rows=\"8\" cols=\"20\"&gt;\nI am a text box.\n</textarea>\n    <input type=\"button\" value=\"Submit\">\n</form>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div><br></div><div><b>Form instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>This example demonstrates how to add a form to a page. This form contains an input box, a text field, a radio button, a check box, a drop-down list, and a confirmation button.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"form.php\" method=\"post\"&gt;\n    Author: &lt;input type = \"text\" name = \"Name\"&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n    Text content:&lt;br/&gt;\n    &lt;textarea rows=\"8\" cols=\"20\"&gt;\n    </textarea><br>\n    <input type=\"radio\" name=\"sex\" value=\"Male\">Male <input type=\"radio\" name=\"sex\" value=\"female\">female<br>\n    <select name=\"degrees\">\n        <option value=\"Primary School\">Primary School</option>\n        <option value=\"junior middle school\">junior high school</option>\n        <option value=\"College\" selected=\"\">College</option>\n        <option value=\"undergraduate\">undergraduate</option>\n        <option value=\"Master\">Master</option>\n        <option value=\"Dr.\">PhD</option>\n    </select>\n    <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">\n</form>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div><br></div><div>Click the \"Submit\" button and the form data will be sent to the form.php page as a post.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>This example demonstrates how to send an email from a form.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code\">\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"form.php\" method=\"post\"&gt;\n    Name:&lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"text\" name=\"name\" &gt;&lt;br&gt;\n    E-mail:&lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"text\" name=\"mail\" &gt;&lt;br&gt;\n    Your opinion:&lt;br&gt;\n   &lt;textarea cols=\"20\" rows=\"2\"&gt;\n   </textarea><br>\n    <input type=\"submit\" value=\"send\">\n    <input type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">\n</form>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div><br></div><div>Click the \"Submit\" button, the form data will be sent to the form.php page as a post. Click the \"Reset\" button to clear the content you entered.</div><br>\n		   <br>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML form |jquerylearn.com', ' form is for collecting different types of user input, such as:HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(82, 7, 'html-iframe', 'HTML iframe', '		  		  		  		  		   <h1>HTML iframe</h1><div><br></div><div>By using the iframe, you can display more than one page in the same browser window.</div><div><br></div><div>Frame label <b>iframe</b></div><div><br></div><h2>Iframe syntax:</h2><div>&lt;iframe src=\"URL\"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</div><div><br></div><div>The URL points to a different web page. Can also point to a specific HTML file</div><div><br></div><div><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 30px;\">Iframe - set height and width</span></div><div><br></div><div>The height and width properties are used to define the height and width of the iframe tag.</div><div><br></div><div>The property defaults to pixels, but you can specify it to be displayed proportionally (eg \"80%\").</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;iframe src=\"https://jquerylearn.com\" width=\"400\" height=\"200\"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;\n&lt;iframe src=\"https://jquerylearn.com\" width=\"400\" height=\"200\"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;\n&lt;p&gt; Some older browsers do not support iframes. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;If the browser does not support iframes, it will not be displayed. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<div><br></div><h2>Iframe - remove the border</h2><div><br></div><div>The frameborder property is used to define whether the iframe represents a border.</div><div><br></div><div>Set the property value to \"0\" to remove the border of the iframe:</div><div><br></div><div>Instance</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;iframe src=\"https://jquerylearn.com\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" frameborder=\"0\"&gt;\n    &lt;p&gt;Your browser does not support iframe tags. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/iframe&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<div>Run this program to see how it differs from the above program.</div><div><br></div><div>Use iframe to display directory link page</div><div><br></div><div>Iframe can display a page with a target link</div><div><br></div><div>The properties of the target link must use the properties of the iframe, as in the following example:</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n    &lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;iframe src=\"https://jquerylearn.com\" name=\"iframe_a\"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=\"https://jquerylearn.com\" target=\"iframe_a\"&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<div>Run the program and click to see</div><div><br></div><h2>HTML iframe tag</h2><div><br></div><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><tbody><tr><td><b>Label<span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; white-space: pre;\">	</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></b></td><td><b>Description</b></td></tr><tr><td>&lt;iframe&gt;</td><td>Define an inline iframe</td></tr></tbody></table><div><br></div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"white-space:pre\">	</span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><br>\n		   <br>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', 'HTML iframe | jquerylearn.com', '  By using the iframe, you can display more than one page in the same browser window.HTML, Tutorial, beginners, develop, website, simple, easy, steps, starting, overview, basic tags, meta tags, attributes, formatting, phrase tags, comments, fonts, marquees, images, links, tables, frames, lists, layouts, colors, forms, backgrounds, style sheet, javascript.', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay');
