ba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;audio&gt;</font></font></td><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Defined sound content</font></font></td></tr><tr style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;source&gt;</font></font></td><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Prescribed multimedia resources, can be multiple, used in the &lt;video&gt; and &lt;audio&gt; tags<br><br></font></font></td></tr></tbody></table></div><div><br></div><div><br></div></div></div>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'html5 audio,html5,html,audio,audio control,html5,audiotag,html5 audio,html audio,html css image', 'HTML5 Audio (audio) | jquerylearn.com', 'HTML5 provides a standard for playing audio files. Until now, there is still no standard for playing audio on web pages.\nToday, most audio is played through plugins such as Flash. However, not all browsers have the same plugin.\nHTML5 specifies the standard for embedding audio elements on web pages, using the <audio> element.', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(96, 8, 'html-input-type', 'HTML5 Input type', '		  		  		  		  		   <div><h1>HTML5 Input type</h1><div>HTML5 has several new form input types. These new features provide better input control and verification.</div><div><br></div><div>This chapter provides a comprehensive introduction to these new input types:</div><div><br></div><div><b>Color</b></div><div><b>Date</b></div><div><b>Datetime</b></div><div><b>Datetime-local</b></div><div><b>Email</b></div><div><b>Month</b></div><div><b>Number</b></div><div><b>Range</b></div><div><b>Search</b></div><div><b>Tel</b></div><div><b>Time</b></div><div><b>Url</b></div><div><b>Week</b></div><div><br></div><div>Note : Not all major browsers support the new input type, but you can already use them in all major browsers. Even if it is not supported, it can still be displayed as a regular text field.</div><div><br></div><h2>Input Type: color</h2><div>The color type used in the input field is mainly used to select the color, as shown below:</div><div><br></div><div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\" \" method=\"post\"&gt;\n    Choose the color you like: &lt;input type=\"color\" name=\"favcolor\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;?php\nEcho $_POST[\'favcolor\'];\n?&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><div><h2>Input type: date</h2><div>The date type allows you to select a date from a date picker.</div></div><div><br></div><div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n&lt;meta charset=\"utf-8\"&gt;\n&lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n  Birthday: &lt;input type=\"date\" name=\"bday\"&gt;\n  &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><br></div><div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><div><h2>Input type: Datetime</h2><div>The datetime type allows you to choose a date (UTC time).</div><div><br></div><div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define a date and time controller (local time):</div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    Birthday (date and time): &lt;input type=\"datetime\" name=\"bdaytime\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>Input type: datetime-local</h2><div>The datetime-local type allows you to choose a date and time (no time zone).</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define a date and time (no time zone):</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    Birthday (date and time): &lt;input type=\"datetime-local\" name=\"bdaytime\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>Input Type: email</h2><div>The email type is used for input fields that should contain an e-mail address.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>When the form is submitted, it automatically verifies that the value of the email domain is legal and valid:</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    E-mail: &lt;input type=\"email\" name=\"usremail\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program to enter a legal and illegal email. Try it out.</div><div><br></div><div>Note : Type=\"email\" is not supported in Internet Explorer 9 and earlier versions of IE.</div><div><br></div><h2>Input type: month</h2><div>The month type allows you to select a month.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define the month and year (no time zone):</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    Birthday (month and year): &lt;input type=\"month\" name=\"bdaymonth\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>Input type: number</h2><div>The number type is used for input fields that should contain numeric values.</div><div><br></div><div>You can also set a limit on the number you accept:</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define a numeric input field (qualified):</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    Quantity (between 1 and 5): &lt;input type=\"number\" name=\"quantity\" min=\"1\" max=\"5\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><div>Use the following properties to specify a limit on the number type:</div><div><br></div><div>Max- specifies the maximum allowed</div><div><br></div><div>Min - specifies the minimum allowed</div><div><br></div><div>Step - specifies a legal number interval (if step=\"3\", the legal number is -3, 0, 3, 6, etc.)</div><div><br></div><div>Value - specifies the default value</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Example with all qualified attributes</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo_form.php\" method=\"get\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"number\" name=\"points\" min=\"0\" max=\"10\" step=\"3\" value=\"6\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>Input type: range</h2><div>The range type is used for input fields that should contain a range of numeric values.</div><div><br></div><div>The range type is displayed as a slider.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define a value that does not require very precise (similar to slider control):</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\" method=\"get\"&gt;\n    Points: &lt;input type=\"range\" name=\"points\" min=\"1\" max=\"10\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><div>Use the following properties to specify a limit on the number type:</div><div><br></div><div>Max - specifies the maximum allowed</div><div><br></div><div>Min - specifies the minimum allowed</div><div><br></div><div>Step - specifies a legal number interval</div><div><br></div><div>Value - specifies the default value</div><div><br></div><h2>Input Type: search</h2><div>The search type is used to search for domains, such as site search or Google search.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define a search field (like site search or Google search):</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    Search Google: &lt;input type=\"search\" name=\"googlesearch\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>Input Type: tel</h2><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define the input phone number field:</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    Phone number: &lt;input type=\"tel\" name=\"usrtel\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>Input type: time</h2><div>The time type allows you to choose a time.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define the input time controller (no time zone):</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    Choose a time: &lt;input type=\"time\" name=\"usr_time\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>Input type: url</h2><div>The url type is used for input fields that should contain a URL address.</div><div><br></div><div>The value of the url field is automatically verified when the form is submitted.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define the input URL field:</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;jquerylearn.com&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n    Add your homepage: &lt;input type=\"url\" name=\"homepage\"&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div><b>Run the program and try it out</b></div><div><br></div><h2>Input type: week</h2><div>The week type allows you to choose weeks and years.</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Define week and year (no time zone):</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form><textarea class=\"code\">&lt;form action=\"demo-form.php\"&gt;\n  Select week: &lt;input type=\"week\" name=\"year_week\"&gt;\n  &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n</textarea></form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><div>HTML5 &lt;input&gt; tag</div><div><br></div><div><table width=\"-642\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(20, 25, 30); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, 微软雅黑, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(237, 241, 242);\"><tbody style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><tr class=\"firstRow\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); word-break: break-all; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 18px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;label</strong></span></td><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); word-break: break-all; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;description</span></strong></td></tr><tr style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); word-break: break-all; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;input&gt;</font></font></td><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); word-break: break-all; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\"><font style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: inherit;\">Describe input input<br><br></font></font></td></tr></tbody></table></div><div>Note : Not all major browsers support the new input type, but you can already use them in all major browsers. Even if it is not supported, it can still be displayed as a regular text field.</div></div></div></div></div></div>\n		   \n		   \n		   \n		   \n		  ', 'input search,types of numbers,html5 email,html type email,html5 input types,input,input type,input type email,html5 form,input type text,input type date,type email,', 'HTML5 Input type | jquerylearn.com', 'HTML5 has several new form input types. These new features provide better input control and verification.This chapter provides a comprehensive introduction to these new input types:\nColor,Date,Datetime,Datetime-local,Email,Month,Number,Range,Search,Tel,Time,Url,Week', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay'),
(97, 8, 'html-new-form-element', 'HTML5 new form elements', '<h1>HTML5 new form element</h1><div><br></div><div><b>&lt;datalist&gt;</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>&lt;keygen&gt;</b></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>&lt;output&gt;</b></div><div><br></div><div><b>Note </b>: Not all browsers support HTML5 new form elements, but you can use them, even if the browser does not support form properties, you can still display them as regular form elements.</div><div><br></div><h2>&lt;datalist&gt; element</h2><div>The &lt;datalist&gt; element specifies a list of options for the input field.</div><div><br></div><div>The &lt;datalist&gt; attribute specifies that the form or input field should have auto-completion. When the user starts typing in the auto-complete field, the browser should display the filled-in options in that field:</div><div><br></div><div>Use the list attribute of the &lt;input&gt; element to bind to the &lt;datalist&gt; element.</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;JQUERYLEARN.COM&lt;/title&gt; \n\n\n&lt;form action=\"\" method=\"get\"&gt;\n    &lt;input list=\"fruits\" name=\"fruit\"&gt;\n    &lt;datalist id=\"fruits\"&gt;\n        &lt;option value=\"Apple\"&gt;\n        &lt;/option&gt;&lt;option value=\"banana\"&gt;\n        &lt;/option&gt;&lt;option value=\"柚子\"&gt;\n        &lt;/option&gt;&lt;option value=\"orange \"&gt;\n        &lt;/option&gt;&lt;option value=\"Pears\"&gt;\n    &lt;/option&gt;&lt;/datalist&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n\n\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>&lt;keygen&gt; element</h2><div><br></div><div>The &lt;keygen&gt; element is used to provide a reliable way to authenticate users.</div><div><br></div><div>The &lt;keygen&gt; tag specifies the key pair generator field for the form.</div><div><br></div><div>When the form is submitted, two keys are generated, one for the private key and one for the public key.</div><div><br></div><div>The private key is stored on the client, and the public key is sent to the server. The public key can be used to later authenticate the user\'s client certificate.</div><div><br></div>\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;JQUERYLEARN.COM&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form action=\"\" method=\"get\"&gt;\n    Username: &lt;input type=\"text\" name=\"usr_name\"&gt;\n    Encryption: &lt;keygen name=\"security\"&gt;\n    &lt;input type=\"submit\"&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; Internet Explorer does not support the keygen tag. &lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<div>Put the program in your editor, try running the program locally.</div><h2>&lt;output&gt; element</h2><div>The &lt;output&gt; element is used for different types of output, such as calculations or script output:</div><div><br></div><div><b>Instance</b></div><div><br></div><div>Display the calculation results in the &lt;output&gt; element:</div><div><br></div>\n\n<form>\n<textarea class=\"code\">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt; \n    &lt;meta charset=\"UTF-8\"&gt;\n    &lt;title&gt;JQUERYLEARN.COM&lt;/title&gt; \n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;form oninput=\"x.value=parseInt(a.value)+parseInt(b.value)\"&gt;0\n    &lt;input type=\"range\" id=\"a\" value=\"50\"&gt;100\n    +&lt;input type=\"number\" id=\"b\" value=\"50\"&gt;\n    =&lt;output name=\"x\" for=\"a b\"&gt;&lt;/output&gt;\n&lt;/form&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;\n\n</textarea>\n</form>\n\n<div>Run the program and try it out</div><div><br></div><h2>HTML5 new form element</h2><div><table width=\"-642\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(20, 25, 30); font-family: &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, 微软雅黑, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; background-color: rgb(237, 241, 242);\"><tbody style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><tr class=\"firstRow\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 18px;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;label</strong></span></td><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); word-break: break-all; border-width: 1px; border-style: solid;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;description</span></td></tr><tr style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; padding: 5px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.6;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; padding: 5px 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &lt;datalist&gt;</span></p></td><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">The &lt;input&gt; tag defines a list of options.</span>&nbsp;<span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">Use this element with the input element to define the possible values ​​for input.</span></td></tr><tr style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;keygen&gt;</span></td><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">The &lt;keygen&gt; tag specifies the key pair generator field for the form.</span></td></tr><tr style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;output&gt;</span></td><td width=\"193\" valign=\"top\" style=\"margin: 0px; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; word-break: break-all;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: inherit;\">The &lt;output&gt; tag defines different types of output, such as the output of a script.</span><br><br></td></tr></tbody></table></div>', 'html5 form,html5 form validation,html5 button,html5 form elements,html5 email validation,html5 required,html5 date,html validator,html5 html tag,how to create a form in html5,html5 intro,html5 forms tutorial', 'HTML5 new form elements | jquerylearn.com', 'HTML 5 , The <input> tag defines a list of options. Use this element with the input element to define the possible values ​​for input.	The <keygen> tag specifies the key pair generator field for the form.	The <output> tag defines different types of output, such as the output of a script.', '2018-07-06 12:32:44', 'akshay');
